register.name: ACTLR_EL1
register.description: Provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED configuration and control options for execution at EL1 and EL0.

register.name: ACTLR_EL2
register.description: Provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED configuration and control options for EL2.

register.name: ACTLR_EL3
register.description: Provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED configuration and control options for EL3.

register.name: CPACR_EL1
register.description: Controls access to trace, and to Advanced SIMD and floating-point functionality.

bitField.name: TTA
bitField.description: Traps EL0 and EL1 System register accesses to all implemented trace registers to EL1, or to EL2 when SCR_EL3.NS is 1 and HCR_EL2.TGE is 1, from both Execution states.

bitField.name: FPEN
bitField.description: Traps EL0 and EL1 accesses to the Advanced SIMD and floating-point registers to EL1, or to EL2 when SCR_EL3.NS is 1 and HCR_EL2.TGE is 1, from both Execution states.

register.name: SCTLR_EL1
register.description: Provides top level control of the system, including its memory system, at EL1 and EL0.

bitField.name: UCI
bitField.description: Traps EL0 execution of cache maintenance instructions to EL1, from AArch64 state only.

bitField.name: EE
bitField.description: Endianness of data accesses at EL1, and stage 1 translation table walks in the EL1&0 translation regime.

bitField.name: E0E
bitField.description: Endianness of data accesses at EL0.

bitField.name: SPAN
bitField.description: Set Privileged Access Never, on taking an exception to EL1.

bitField.name: WXN
bitField.description: Write permission implies XN (Execute-never). For the EL1&0 translation regime, this bit can force all memory regions that are writable to be treated as XN.

bitField.name: nTWE
bitField.description: Traps EL0 execution of WFE instructions to EL1, from both Execution states.

bitField.name: nTWI
bitField.description: Traps EL0 execution of WFI instructions to EL1, from both Execution states.

bitField.name: UCT
bitField.description: Traps EL0 accesses to the CTR_EL0 to EL1, from AArch64 state only.

bitField.name: DZE
bitField.description: Traps EL0 execution of DC ZVA instructions to EL1, from AArch64 state only.

bitField.name: I
bitField.description: Instruction access Cacheability control, for accesses at EL0 and EL1:

bitField.name: UMA
bitField.description: User Mask Access. Traps EL0 execution of MSR and MRS instructions that access the PSTATE.{D, A, I, F} masks to EL1, from AArch64 state only.

bitField.name: SED
bitField.description: SETEND instruction disable. Disables SETEND instructions at EL0 using AArch32.

bitField.name: ITD
bitField.description: IT Disable. Disables some uses of IT instructions at EL0 using AArch32.

bitField.name: CP15BEN
bitField.description: System instruction memory barrier enable.

bitField.name: SA0
bitField.description: SP Alignment check enable for EL0. When set to 1, if a load or store instruction executed at EL0 uses the SP as the base address and the SP is not aligned to a 16-byte boundary, then a SP alignment fault exception is generated. For more information, see .

bitField.name: SA
bitField.description: SP Alignment check enable. When set to 1, if a load or store instruction executed at EL1 uses the SP as the base address and the SP is not aligned to a 16-byte boundary, then a SP alignment fault exception is generated. For more information, see .

bitField.name: C
bitField.description: Cacheability control, for data accesses.

bitField.name: A
bitField.description: Alignment check enable.

bitField.name: M
bitField.description: MMU enable for EL1 and EL0 stage 1 address translation.

register.name: SCTLR_EL2
register.description: Provides top level control of the system, including its memory system, at EL2...

bitField.name: WXN
bitField.description: Write permission implies XN (Execute-never). For the EL2 or EL2&0 translation regime, this bit can force all memory regions that are writable to be treated as XN.

bitField.name: SA
bitField.description: SP Alignment check enable. When set to 1, if a load or store instruction executed at EL2 uses the SP as the base address and the SP is not aligned to a 16-byte boundary, then a SP alignment fault exception is generated. For more information, see .

bitField.name: C
bitField.description: Cacheability control, for data accesses.

bitField.name: A
bitField.description: Alignment check enable.

register.name: SCTLR_EL3
register.description: Provides top level control of the system, including its memory system, at EL3.

bitField.name: EE
bitField.description: Endianness of data accesses at EL3, and stage 1 translation table walks in the EL3 translation regime.

bitField.name: WXN
bitField.description: Write permission implies XN (Execute-never). For the EL3 translation regime, this bit can force all memory regions that are writable to be treated as XN.

bitField.name: I
bitField.description: Instruction access Cacheability control, for accesses at EL3:

bitField.name: SA
bitField.description: SP Alignment check enable. When set to 1, if a load or store instruction executed at EL3 uses the SP as the base address and the SP is not aligned to a 16-byte boundary, then a SP alignment fault exception is generated. For more information, see .

bitField.name: C
bitField.description: Cacheability control, for data accesses.

bitField.name: A
bitField.description: Alignment check enable.

bitField.name: M
bitField.description: MMU enable for EL3 stage 1 address translation.
